dcterms:description: An extensive benchmark for scientific machine learning, providing a comprehensive dataset for evaluating machine learning models on partial differential equations.
dcterms:title: PDEBench

dcterms:description: A dataset created by the authors containing 25.6K PDEs for their experiments, equipped with 20 initial conditions for each PDE.
dcterms:title: Various PDEs (25.6K PDEs dataset)

dcterms:description: A method used for generating initial conditions rather than a standalone dataset.
dcterms:title: Gaussian Process

dcterms:description: Describes the methodology for generating initial conditions for different types of equations rather than a specific dataset.
dcterms:title: Various initial conditions for different types of equations

dcterms:description: Describes experimental setups involving simulations with single observed shocks and mixtures of shocks and rarefactions.
dcterms:title: Simulations with single observed shocks and mixtures of shocks and rarefactions

dcterms:description: Describes a specific experimental setup for testing the Riemann problem rather than a standalone dataset.
dcterms:title: Riemann problem for testing
